      note:"أَل is Arabic's only article. When it precedes a 'sun letter' (14 letters including ت ش س ن ر), the ل assimilates into that letter. This is pronunciation only — spelling always shows أَل. ★ SUN/MOON DRILL: Add أَل to these 8 words and pronounce correctly: شَمْس، قَمَر، نَهْر، سَمَاء، دَرْس، طَالِب، رَجُل، نُور. Mark each S (sun) or M (moon)."
