    culture:{title:"الاسْم العَرَبِيّ وَمَعْنَاه -- Arabic Names and their Meanings",body:"Arabic names carry meaning. مُحَمَّد (the most praised), فَاطِمَة (she who weans), عَبْدُ الله (servant of God), نُور (light), جَمَال (beauty). Naming follows patterns: عَبْد + one of God\'s 99 names (عَبْد الرَّحْمَن, عَبْد الكَرِيم). Family names often indicate origin (الشَّامِيّ = from Syria), profession (الحَدَّاد = the blacksmith), or a famous ancestor. In Arab tradition, the full name chain (نَسَب) connects you to your grandfather: أَحْمَد بْن مُحَمَّد بْن عَلِيّ.",tip:"The tasmiya (تَسْمِيَة = naming ceremony) happens 7 days after birth, with a sheep slaughtered (عَقِيقَة) and the name announced. Names are chosen for beauty of meaning, religious significance, or family legacy."},
