    id:5,title:"The Family",culture:{title:"بَيْتُ العَائِلَة العَرَبِيّ — The Arab Family Home",body:"In Arab culture, it is very common for multiple generations to live under one roof. Sons may stay with their parents after marriage. A daughter traditionally lives with her parents until she marries and moves to her husband's home. When an Arab invites you in, they may insist you enter first — respond by saying لَا، أَنْتَ أَوَّلًا (No, you first). The elder or senior person ultimately goes first. Always remove shoes when entering a home unless told otherwise.",tip:"الجَارُ قَبْلَ الدَّار — the neighbour before the house. This proverb means: choose your neighbourhood before your house."},arabic:"العَائِلَة",
