  {type:"mcq",q:"What time does Layla wake up each morning?",opts:["5am","6am","7am","8am"],ans:1,exp:"The passage says تَسْتَيْقِظُ لَيْلَى فِي السَّاعَة السَّادِسَة صَبَاحاً — she wakes at 6am."},
  {type:"tf",q:"Layla studies medicine at university.",ans:1,exp:"FALSE — Layla studies Arabic literature (الأَدَب العَرَبِيّ). She wants to become a teacher (مُعَلِّمَة) in the future."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"What does أَوَّلًا mean in the context of daily routine?",opts:["Finally","Then","First","Always"],ans:2,exp:"أَوَّلًا = first — the first time-order word. Used to begin a sequence: أَوَّلًا... ثُمَّ... أَخِيراً = first... then... finally."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"Form I verb أَسْتَيْقِظُ belongs to which derived form?",opts:["Form I","Form V","Form VIII","Form X"],ans:3,exp:"أَسْتَيْقِظُ = I wake up, from the root ي-ق-ظ. This is Form X (اِسْتَيْقَظَ = to wake up, literally 'to seek wakefulness')."}
