  {type:"mcq",q:"How many bedrooms does the house in the passage have?",opts:["Two","Three","Four","Five"],ans:2,exp:"The passage describes ثَلَاث غُرَف نَوْم (three bedrooms) in the family house."},
  {type:"tf",q:"In an iḍāfa construction, the first noun can take the definite article أَل.",ans:1,exp:"FALSE — in iḍāfa, the FIRST noun never takes أَل. غُرْفَة النَّوْم (room of sleeping = bedroom) — غُرْفَة is indefinite."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"The word مَطْبَخ means...",opts:["Bathroom","Bedroom","Kitchen","Living room"],ans:2,exp:"مَطْبَخ = kitchen, from the root ط-ب-خ (to cook). It is a place-noun (اسم مكان) from Form II."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"Where is the balcony according to the passage?",opts:["Next to the kitchen","Above the garage","Overlooking the garden","At the entrance"],ans:2,exp:"The passage says شُرْفَة تُطِلّ عَلَى الحَدِيقَة — a balcony overlooking the garden."}
