    id:8,title:"The Neighbourhood",culture:{title:"المَقْهَى وَالحَيّ — Coffee House & Neighbourhood Culture",body:"The Arabic مَقْهَى (café/coffee house) is the heartbeat of the Arab neighbourhood. Men gather here to drink شَاي (tea) or قَهْوَة (coffee), play backgammon (طَاوِلَة), and discuss politics, sports, and family. In Egypt it's called the أَهْوَة — from قَهْوَة with ق→أ shift. The concept of sitting for hours without obligation to buy more is deeply Arab. Nobody rushes you.",tip:"تَفَضَّل اِجْلِس — Please sit down. The verb تَفَضَّل is used constantly in Arab hospitality contexts."},arabic:"الحَيّ وَالجِوَار",
