  {type:"mcq",q:"What does حَيّ mean?",opts:["Street","Neighbourhood","City","Country"],ans:1,exp:"حَيّ (pl. أَحْيَاء) = neighbourhood — a district within a city. مُدِيرِيَّة = governorate; مَدِينَة = city."},
  {type:"tf",q:"The nisba suffix ـِيّ creates nouns, not adjectives.",ans:1,exp:"FALSE — ـِيّ creates ADJECTIVES (nisba adjectives): شَعْبِيّ = popular/of the people; مِصْرِيّ = Egyptian. They can function as nouns secondarily."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"What service is located near Ahmad's home according to the passage?",opts:["School only","Mosque and pharmacy","Hospital and stadium","Airport and port"],ans:1,exp:"The passage mentions a mosque (مَسْجِد) and pharmacy (صَيْدَلِيَّة) near Ahmad's neighbourhood."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"قَرِيب مِن means...",opts:["Far from","In the middle of","Near to","Behind"],ans:2,exp:"قَرِيب مِن = near to, close to. Its antonym is بَعِيد عَن = far from."}
