      note:"The nisba suffix ـِيّ turns any noun into a relational adjective. Add to countries, cities, materials, concepts. Feminine: add ة → ـِيَّة. Plural for humans: ـِيُّون (m) / ـِيَّات (f). ★ NISBA DRILL: Form nisba adjectives from: مِصْر، لُبْنَان، الكُوَيْت، عَمَّان، بَيْرُوت، الجَزَائِر. Give m and f forms. ★ FILL-IN: هُوَ مِن الأُرْدُن، إِذَن هُوَ ___."
