  {type:"tf",q:"يَوْم الجُمْعَة is the day of Friday prayers in Islam.",ans:0,exp:"TRUE — الجُمْعَة (Friday) comes from اجتماع (gathering). It is the Islamic holy day of congregational prayer."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"How many months does the Gregorian year have?",opts:["Ten","Eleven","Twelve","Thirteen"],ans:2,exp:"اِثْنَا عَشَر شَهْراً = twelve months in the Gregorian (مِيلَادِيّ) calendar, as in the Islamic calendar."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"The nominal sentence in Arabic...",opts:["Always requires a verb","Has subject + predicate only, no verb needed","Uses كَانَ as its main verb","Only works in past tense"],ans:1,exp:"A nominal sentence (جُمْلَة اسْمِيَّة) needs only مُبْتَدَأ + خَبَر — there is no 'to be' in Arabic present tense."}
