    id:14,title:"Clothing & Colours",arabic:"المَلَابِس وَالأَلْوَان",
    culture:{title:"اللِّبَاس العَرَبِيّ -- Dress in the Arab World",body:"Arab dress varies by country and context. Gulf men wear the traditional ثَوْب (dishdasha) in white. Levantine and North African dress is more Mediterranean in style. The حِجَاب (headscarf) is worn by many Muslim women but is not universal across the Arab world. The كُوفِيَّة (keffiyeh) is a powerful symbol of Palestinian identity. Colours carry strong cultural associations: أَبْيَض (white) for purity and peace, أَخْضَر (green) for Islam.",tip:"لَوْنَك وِحْشَنِي (Egyptian) literally means \'I miss your colour\', meaning \'I miss you\'. Colours in Arabic often carry emotional weight beyond their visual meaning."},
