    culture:{title:"خُلَاصَة الرُّبْع الأَوَّل -- End of Q1",body:"By Q1 you have the tools for basic Arabic conversation and cultural navigation. The most important lesson from Q1: Arabic greetings are investments, not formalities. Every salam you give and receive builds a relationship. Arab culture tracks these social investments and responds in kind. Never rush a greeting -- it is rude. Q2 will add geography, shopping, numbers, and the full present tense.",tip:"Li-kull maqam maqal (for every situation there is a saying) -- this proverb captures how Arabic culture prizes the right words at the right time. Q1 vocabulary gives you the speech; culture notes teach you when to use it."},
