      note:"★ KEY RULE: (1) Past tense — consonant suffixes SHORTEN the long vowel: قَالَ → قُلْتُ (waw root gives ū); بَاعَ → بِعْتُ (yā root gives ī); نَامَ → نِمْتُ (waw root here gives ī — exceptions exist). (2) Present tense — the original middle radical REAPPEARS: يَقُولُ (و visible), يَبِيعُ (ي visible). ★ PRODUCTION DRILL A: Given root ز-و-ر (visit), past زَارَ — produce the present tense for all 8 pronouns above. ★ PRODUCTION DRILL B: Given roots ق-و-م (rise), س-ي-ر (travel), ف-ا-ز (win from ف-و-ز) — fill the paradigm for past and present. ★ SENTENCE DRILL C: Complete with correct present tense — يَا وَلَد، فِي أَيِّ سَاعَة ___ (نَوم)؟ · هِيَ ___ السَّيَّارَات (بيع) فِي هَذَا الدُّكَّان. · نَحْنُ دَائِمًا ___ (قول) الحَقِيقَة."
