    culture:{title:"الوَاسِطَة -- Connections and Social Capital",body:"الوَاسِطَة (wasta) is the Arab concept of using personal connections to get things done. Finding a job, getting a hospital appointment, solving bureaucratic problems -- having the right connections is invaluable. It reflects the Arab priority of collective networks (العَلَاقَات الاجْتِمَاعِيَّة) over impersonal systems. Having a well-connected uncle (عَمّ فِيهِ وَاسِطَة) is genuinely advantageous and not seen as corruption.",tip:"The most prestigious professions in Arab culture: طَبِيب (doctor), مُهَنْدِس (engineer), مُحَامٍ (lawyer). Asking someone\'s profession very early in conversation is completely normal."},
