  {type:"mcq",q:"Which Arab country has the longest coastline?",opts:["مِصْر","السَّعُودِيَّة","المَغْرِب","عُمَان"],ans:1,exp:"Saudi Arabia has the longest coastline among Arab countries, with coasts on both the Red Sea (البَحْر الأَحْمَر) and the Arabian Gulf (الخَلِيج العَرَبِيّ)."}
