    culture:{title:"تَنَوُّع العَالَم العَرَبِيّ -- Diversity Within Unity",body:"The 22 Arab states share language and many cultural values, but are remarkably diverse. Morocco\'s Amazigh (Berber) populations predate the Arab conquest. Lebanon is about 40% Christian. Bahrain\'s majority is Shia Muslim under Sunni rule. Egypt has 100 million people; Qatar has fewer than 300,000 citizens. The Arab world stretches across 5 time zones. Arabic was the language of medieval science -- the words algebra (الجَبْر), alcohol (الكُحُول), almanac (المَنَاخ), and chemistry (الكِيمِيَاء) all come from Arabic.",tip:"The Arabic word عَرَبِيّ (Arab) originally referred to nomadic Bedouin tribes. The definition of who is Arab is cultural and linguistic, not racial. Anyone who identifies with Arab culture and speaks Arabic as a mother tongue may call themselves Arab."},
