  {type:"mcq",q:"What is the broken plural of شَقَّة (apartment)?",opts:["شَقَّات","شُقَق","أَشْقَاق","شَقَّاوَات"],ans:1,exp:"شُقَق = apartments (broken plural of شَقَّة, following the فُعَل pattern). Broken plurals restructure the vowels internally unlike sound plurals."},
  {type:"tf",q:"Non-human broken plurals take feminine singular adjective agreement in Arabic.",ans:0,exp:"TRUE — شُقَق جَمِيلَة (beautiful apartments) — جَمِيلَة is feminine singular agreeing with the non-human broken plural. This applies to ALL non-human plurals."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"What does وَدِيعَة mean in rental context?",opts:["Monthly rent","Security deposit","Maintenance fee","Contract"],ans:1,exp:"وَدِيعَة = deposit/security deposit (from وَدَعَ = to entrust/deposit). Also: العَرْبُون = down payment."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"A مُؤَثَّث apartment is...",opts:["Empty / unfurnished","On the ground floor","Furnished","Available immediately"],ans:2,exp:"مُؤَثَّث = furnished (passive participle of أَثَّثَ, Form II). غَيْر مُؤَثَّث = unfurnished. مُجَهَّز = equipped."}
