      note:"Case endings are pronounced in formal speech and written in the Quran and textbooks. Key: مَرْفُوع (subject) = damma; مَجْرُور (after prepositions) = kasra; مَنْصُوب (object/adverb) = fatha. ★ CASE DRILL: Identify the case: كَتَبَ الطَّالِبُ الدَّرْسَ فِي المَكْتَبَةِ — label subject, object, after-preposition. ★ FILL-IN: أَكَلَ الوَلَدُ ___ (add tanwin fatha to التُّفَّاح as object)."
