    comprehension:[
  {type:"mcq",q:"Numbers 11-19 are grammatically special because they...",opts:["Never change form","Always take broken plural","Are indeclinable (always fatḥa) and take singular accusative noun","Follow gender polarity like 3-10"],ans:2,exp:"Numbers 11-19 are مَبْنِيّ (indeclinable — always fatḥa) and the counted noun is SINGULAR ACCUSATIVE: خَمْسَةَ عَشَرَ كِتَاباً (15 books — كِتَاباً = singular acc)."},
  {type:"tf",q:"إِحْدَى عَشْرَة is used when counting feminine nouns.",ans:0,exp:"TRUE — إِحْدَى عَشْرَة طَالِبَة (11 female students). The units part of 11-19 follows polarity: for feminine nouns, unit uses masculine form (and vice versa). It gets complex!"},
  {type:"mcq",q:"Based on the passage, what was the main function of the ancient Arabic numerals before spreading to Europe?",opts:["Only for religious texts","For trade calculations and astronomy","Only for counting people","For decorating manuscripts"],ans:1,exp:"The passage indicates Arab scholars used and developed numerals for trade (تِجَارَة) and astronomy (فَلَك) before transmitting them to Europe via Al-Andalus."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"Which sentence correctly uses a number 11-19?",opts:["ثَلَاثَةَ عَشَرَ كُتُب","ثَلَاثَةَ عَشَرَ كِتَاباً","ثَلَاثَ عَشَرَ كِتَاب","ثَلَاثَ عَشَرَ كِتَاباً"],ans:1,exp:"ثَلَاثَةَ عَشَرَ كِتَاباً = 13 books. ثَلَاثَةَ عَشَرَ (masculine unit for masculine noun? Wait — 13 with masculine noun uses masculine unit: ثَلَاثَةَ عَشَرَ). Noun = singular accusative كِتَاباً."}
,
      {type:"fitb",q:"خَمسَةَ _____ كِتَابًا — complete (15 books)",blank:"عَشَرَ",opts:["عَشَرَ","عَشَرَةَ","عَشرَة"],exp:"11-19: both components must agree. خَمسَة with مُذَكَّر takes عَشَرَ."},
      {type:"mcq",q:"Numbers 11-19 govern their nouns in what case?",opts:["Genitive plural","Accusative singular (tamyiz)","Nominative plural","Idafa construction"],ans:1,exp:"11-99 take the accusative singular as a tamyiz: خَمسَةَ عَشَرَ طَالِبًا."}],
