    comprehension:[
  {type:"mcq",q:"What happens to the ن of the sound masculine plural in iḍāfa?",opts:["It doubles","It disappears (is dropped)","It becomes a long vowel","Nothing changes"],ans:1,exp:"The ن of the sound masculine plural is DROPPED in iḍāfa: مُعَلِّمُو المَدْرَسَة (teachers of the school) not مُعَلِّمُون. This is called حَذْف النُّون لِلإِضَافَة."},
  {type:"tf",q:"Mansaf is the national dish of Jordan.",ans:0,exp:"TRUE — المَنْسَف = lamb cooked in dried yoghurt (جَمِيد) served over rice and flatbread. It is the national dish of Jordan and a symbol of Bedouin hospitality."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"What does يَسْلُق mean?",opts:["He fries","He grills","He boils","He bakes"],ans:2,exp:"يَسْلُق = he boils (from سَلَقَ / يَسْلُق). يَقْلِي = fries. يَشْوِي = grills. يَخْبِز = bakes bread. يُقَلِّي = deep fries."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"Based on the recipe passage, what is the critical step before serving?",opts:["Boiling the rice separately","Adding yoghurt after cooking","Garnishing with almonds and parsley","Marinating the meat overnight"],ans:2,exp:"The passage describes the final step of تَزْيِين بِاللَّوْز وَالبَقْدُونِس (garnishing with almonds and parsley) before serving — a key aesthetic element of the dish."}
,
      {type:"fitb",q:"مُعَلِّم → _____ (sound masculine plural, nominative case)",blank:"مُعَلِّمُونَ",opts:["مُعَلِّمُونَ","مُعَلِّمِينَ","مُعَلِّمَات"],exp:"Sound masculine plural nominative = ـُونَ. Oblique/accusative = ـِينَ."},
      {type:"mcq",q:"Which plural type changes the internal vowel pattern?",opts:["Sound masculine","Sound feminine","Broken plural","Dual"],ans:2,exp:"Broken plurals change the internal pattern (كَتَبَة, كُتُب) — unlike sound plurals which add suffixes."}],
    grammar:[{
      title:"Sound Masculine Plural & Dual",
      type:"table",
      headers:["Form","Nominative","Genitive/Accusative","Example"],
      rows:[
        ["Sound masc pl","ـُون","ـِين","مُعَلِّمُون / مُعَلِّمِين"],
        ["Sound fem pl","ـَات","ـَات","وَصَفَات (recipes)"],
        ["Masc dual","ـَانِ","ـَيْن","طَبَقَانِ / طَبَقَيْن"],
        ["Fem dual","ـَتَانِ","ـَتَيْن","وَصْفَتَانِ / وَصْفَتَيْن"],
        ["Iḍāfa: ن drops","مُعَلِّمُو المَدْرَسَة","teachers of school","ن removed before iḍāfa"]
      ],
      note:"Sound masculine plural (ـُون/ـِين) for male humans. Sound feminine plural (ـَات) for many nouns. The dual marks exactly two. In iḍāfa, the ن of masculine plural and dual is dropped. ★ PLURAL DRILL: Form the sound masculine plural (ـُون/ـِين) of: مُعَلِّم، طَالِب، مُهَنْدِس، مُسَافِر. Then the dual of: كِتَاب، بَيْت، طَالِب. ★ FILL-IN: هُمَا طَالِبَـ___ (dual suffix)."
    }],
