    culture:{title:"كُرَة القَدَم -- Football in the Arab World",body:"Football (كُرَة القَدَم) is the Arab world dominant sport. Egypt\'s national team (الفَرَاعِنَة) won the Africa Cup of Nations 7 times. Morocco reached the 2022 World Cup semi-finals. Arabic football commentary is famous: when a goal is scored, commentators shout a long GOOOAL (هَدَف!) for up to 30 seconds. Traditional Arab sports include الفُرُوسِيَّة (equestrian), صَيْد الصُّقُور (falconry -- UNESCO heritage), and المُصَارَعَة (wrestling).",tip:"The Qatar 2022 World Cup was the first held in an Arab country and the first in the Middle East. It sparked enormous Arab pride across the region regardless of national allegiances."},
