    culture:{title:"المَلَكِيَّات العَرَبِيَّة -- Arab Monarchies",body:"Eight Arab states are monarchies: Saudi Arabia (آل سُعُود), Jordan (الهَاشِمِيُّون), Morocco (عَلَوِيُّون), UAE, Bahrain, Kuwait, Qatar, Oman. The Jordanian and Moroccan royal families trace descent to the Prophet Muhammad through his daughter فَاطِمَة -- giving them special religious legitimacy. Gulf monarchies accumulated enormous wealth after the oil boom of the 1970s. The Saudi King holds the title خَادِم الحَرَمَيْن الشَّرِيفَيْن (Custodian of the Two Holy Mosques).",tip:"The term شَيْخ (sheikh) has different meanings: in Gulf states, a member of a royal or ruling family; in religious contexts, a respected scholar; in tribal contexts, a tribal leader. Context is everything."},
