    comprehension:[
  {type:"mcq",q:"لَا النَّاهِيَة (prohibitive لَا) + verb uses which mood?",opts:["Indicative","Past","Jussive","Subjunctive"],ans:2,exp:"لَا النَّاهِيَة + jussive = prohibition (do not!). لَا تَنْسَ = do not forget! (jussive of يَنْسَى). Compare: لَا يَنْسَى = he does not forget (indicative with different meaning)."},
  {type:"tf",q:"The Hashemite royal family rules Saudi Arabia.",ans:1,exp:"FALSE — الهَاشِمِيُّون rule Jordan (since 1921). آل سَعُود rule Saudi Arabia. The Hashemites claim descent from the Prophet Muhammad (ص) through his grandson Hasan."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"What is a 'Majlis al-Sulṭān' and what does it demonstrate?",opts:["A royal palace","An open audience where citizens can address the ruler directly — demonstrating accessibility","A military council","A religious court"],ans:1,exp:"مَجْلِس السُّلْطَان = open audience — a tradition where citizens approach the ruler with petitions. It demonstrates the Islamic tradition of الشُّورَى (consultation) embedded in Arab governance."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"Infer: What role do royal families play in Arab societies according to the passage?",opts:["Pure ceremonial roles only","They combine traditional tribal authority with modern state governance","They have no real political power","They only manage religious affairs"],ans:1,exp:"The passage presents Arab royal families as combining قِيَادَة قَبَلِيَّة (tribal leadership tradition) with حُكُومَة حَدِيثَة (modern governance) — they are simultaneously symbolic, political, and social anchors."}
,
      {type:"fitb",q:"إِذَا _____ بِجِدٍّ، فَسَتَنجَح. (you study — real condition)",blank:"دَرَستَ",opts:["دَرَستَ","تَدرُسُ","دَرَستُ"],exp:"إِذَا + past tense = real condition. The result (apodosis) uses سَـ + present."},
      {type:"mcq",q:"لَو دَرَستَ لَنَجَحتَ implies?",opts:["You studied and passed","You will study","You did not study (hypothetical past)","You should study now"],ans:2,exp:"لَو introduces hypothetical/counterfactual: if you had studied, you would have passed (but you didn't)."}],
