    comprehension:[
  {type:"mcq",q:"تَمَّ + masdar expresses which meaning?",opts:["Failure to do something","Was completed / came to pass","Will be done","Is being done currently"],ans:1,exp:"تَمَّ + masdar = was completed / took place. تَمَّ الاجتماع = the meeting was completed/held. تَمَّ عَقْد الزَّوَاج = the marriage contract was concluded. A formal alternative to the passive."},
  {type:"tf",q:"Henna night (لَيْلَة الحِنَّاء) is a pre-wedding celebration for men.",ans:1,exp:"FALSE — لَيْلَة الحِنَّاء is a PRE-WEDDING female celebration where women apply henna (decorative plant dye) to the bride's hands and feet. Men have their own separate gathering."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"What is مَهْر in the context of Arab marriage?",opts:["The wedding party venue","The bride-price/dowry — a mandatory gift from groom to bride","The wedding invitation card","The religious ceremony"],ans:1,exp:"المَهْر = bride price/dowry — an obligatory gift from the groom (العَرِيس) to the bride (العَرُوس) as part of the Islamic marriage contract (عَقْد الزَّوَاج). It is legally hers."},
  {type:"ar",q:"ما الفارق الرئيسي بين الأعراس الخليجية والأعراس اللبنانية كما ورد في النص؟",opts:["الخليجية أطول","الخليجية منفصلة للرجال والنساء أما اللبنانية فمختلطة","اللبنانية أكثر تكلفة","الخليجية بدون موسيقى"],ans:1,exp:"النص يوضح أن الأعراس الخليجية تُقام منفصلة (رجال وحدهم، نساء وحدهن) بينما الأعراس اللبنانية والشامية عادةً مختلطة. ويظهر الفارق أيضاً في نوع الموسيقى والرقصات التقليدية."}
,
      {type:"fitb",q:"_____ التَّوقِيعُ — (The signing was completed — use تَمَّ)",blank:"تَمَّ",opts:["تَمَّ","قَامَ","صَارَ"],exp:"تَمَّ / يَتِمُّ + مَصدَر = to be completed. تَمَّ التَّوقِيعُ = The signing was done."},
      {type:"mcq",q:"What grammatical role does the masdar play after تَمَّ?",opts:["Subject (فَاعِل)","Object (مَفعُول)","Predicate (خَبَر)","Circumstantial (حَال)"],ans:0,exp:"After تَمَّ, the masdar is the فَاعِل (subject): تَمَّ التَّوقِيعُ."}],
    grammar:[{
      title:"tamma / yatimmu + Masdar — تَمَّ / يَتِمّ + مَصْدَر",
      type:"table",
      headers:["Structure","Arabic example","Translation","Notes"],
      rows:[
        ["تَمَّ + masdar","تَمَّ الحَفْل","The celebration took place","elegant passive equivalent"],
        ["يَتِمّ + masdar","يَتِمُّ الاحْتِفَال غَدًا","The celebration will take place tomorrow","formal present/future"],
        ["تَمَّ إِرْسَال","تَمَّ إِرْسَالُ الدَّعْوَة","The invitation was sent","tamma + sending-masdar"],
        ["تَمَّ التَّوَصُّل إِلَى","تَمَّ التَّوَصُّل إِلَى اتِّفَاق","An agreement was reached","journalism/formal"],
        ["Compare passive","أُرْسِلَتِ الدَّعْوَة","The invitation was sent","direct passive voice"]
      ],
      note:"تَمَّ + masdar is a sophisticated passive-equivalent used constantly in formal Arabic, journalism, and official speech. Instead of the passive أُرْسِلَتِ الرِّسَالَة, you say تَمَّ إِرْسَالُ الرِّسَالَة (the sending of the letter was completed). This construction appears in every newspaper, every official announcement. Learn it and you will sound like an educated Arab writer. ★ TAMM DRILL: Rewrite these using تَمَّ + masdar: عَقَدُوا الاتِّفَاقِيَّة → تَمَّ عَقْد الاتِّفَاقِيَّة. Practise with: حَضَّرُوا المَنْسَف، بَنَوْا المَسْجِد، افْتَتَحُوا المَعْرِض."
    }],
