    comprehension:[
  {type:"mcq",q:"The passive past tense in Arabic uses which vowel pattern?",opts:["فَعَلَ (a-a)","فُعِلَ (u-i)","فِعِلَ (i-i)","فُعَلَ (u-a)"],ans:1,exp:"Passive past = فُعِلَ (u-i): كُتِبَ (was written), نُشِرَ (was published). Passive present = يُفْعَل: يُكْتَب (is written). Arabic passive is formed by internal vowel change — no auxiliary verb."},
  {type:"tf",q:"The word 'algebra' comes from an Arabic word.",ans:0,exp:"TRUE — 'Algebra' comes from الجَبْر (al-jabr = completion/reduction), from the title of Al-Khwarizmi's 9th century book. Similarly, 'algorithm' comes from his Latinised name Algoritmi."},
  {type:"mcq",q:"What was Bayt al-Hikma (بَيْت الحِكْمَة)?",opts:["A palace in Baghdad","The world's greatest library and translation centre during the Islamic Golden Age","A religious seminary","A military academy"],ans:1,exp:"بَيْت الحِكْمَة (House of Wisdom) in Baghdad was the greatest intellectual institution of its time (8th-13th c), where scholars translated Greek, Persian, and Indian works into Arabic and made original discoveries."},
  {type:"ar",q:"لماذا تُسمَّى الأرقام التي نستخدمها اليوم «أرقاماً عربية» رغم أنها هندية الأصل؟",opts:["لأن العرب اخترعوها","لأن العرب نقلوها من الهند وطوّروها ونشروها في أوروبا","لأن الصفر عربي بالكامل","لأن التسمية خاطئة"],ans:1,exp:"العرب لم يخترعوا الأرقام بل نقلوها من الهند (خاصةً علماء مثل الخوارزمي)، طوّروها، ونقلوها إلى أوروبا عبر الأندلس. لهذا سُمِّيَت عربية تكريماً لدور العرب الوسيط الحضاري."}
,
      {type:"fitb",q:"كَتَبَ الطَّالِبُ الرِّسَالَةَ → passive: _____",blank:"كُتِبَتِ الرِّسَالَةُ",opts:["كُتِبَتِ الرِّسَالَةُ","تُكتَبُ الرِّسَالَةُ","الرِّسَالَةُ كَتَبَت"],exp:"Past passive: change vowels to ـُـ on first radical, ـِـ before last: كَتَبَ → كُتِبَ."},
      {type:"mcq",q:"How is the past passive formed in Form I?",opts:["CaCaCa → CuCiCa","Add مَـ prefix","Change to CaCCāC","No vowel change"],ans:0,exp:"Past passive pattern: CuCiCa — change first vowel to damma, middle vowel to kasra."}],
    grammar:[{
      title:"The Passive Voice — المَبْنِيّ لِلْمَجْهُول",
      type:"table",
      headers:["Active","Passive (past)","Passive (present)","Meaning"],
      rows:[
        ["كَتَبَ الطَّالِب الكِتَاب","كُتِبَ الكِتَاب","يُكْتَب الكِتَاب","The book was/is written"],
        ["اِبْتَكَرَ الجَبْر","اُبْتُكِرَ الجَبْر","يُبْتَكَر","Algebra was invented"],
        ["وَضَعَ الأَسَاس","وُضِعَ الأَسَاس","يُوضَع","The foundation was laid"],
        ["نَقَلَ العِلْم","نُقِلَ العِلْم","يُنْقَل","Knowledge was transferred"],
        ["Pattern: past","فُعِلَ (u-i pattern)","يُفْعَل","internal vowel change"]
      ],
      note:"The passive voice in Arabic changes internal vowels — no auxiliary verb needed. Past: فَعَلَ → فُعِلَ (u-i): كَتَبَ → كُتِبَ. Present: يَفْعَلُ → يُفْعَلُ (u throughout): يَكْتُبُ → يُكْتَبُ. The subject of the active sentence disappears; the object becomes the 'naib al-fail' (subject of passive), which takes nominative case. ★ PASSIVE VOICE DRILL: Convert to passive: كَتَبَ الطَّالِب الدَّرْسَ → كُتِبَ الدَّرْسُ. Practise: فَتَحَ المُدِير البَاب، بَنَوْا المَسْجِد، يَعْرِف الجَمِيع الحَقِيقَة. ★ FILL-IN: الكِتَاب ___ (was published) في القاهرة."
    }],
    speaking:{topic:"Speak about an Arab contribution to civilisation", promptAr:"تَكَلَّم عَن إِسْهَام عَرَبِيّ فِي الحَضَارَة", promptEn:"Record 90 seconds: choose one Arab or Islamic scholar from history. Explain what they contributed, when and where they lived, and how their work influences us today. Use passive voice at least twice."},
