    id:47, title:"Radio Broadcasts & Listening Skills", arabic:"البَثُّ الإِذَاعِيّ وَمَهَارَات الاِسْتِمَاع",
    culture:{title:"الإِذَاعَة وَالإِعْلَام العَرَبِيّ -- Arab Radio and Media",body:"Arabic radio has a special place in Arab cultural memory. صَوْتُ العَرَب (Voice of the Arabs, Cairo 1953) was pan-Arab radio at its height -- Nasser\'s voice uniting the Arab world. بِي بِي سِي عَرَبِيّ (BBC Arabic, est. 1938) is the oldest and most trusted Arab broadcaster. Today الجَزِيرَة (Al Jazeera) and عَرَبِيَّة (Al Arabiya) dominate satellite TV. Arabic podcasts (بُودْكَاسْت عَرَبِيّ) have exploded -- يَلَّا نِحْكِي (Yalla Nehki), مَشْرُوع مِدْيَا (Mashrou\' Media).",tip:"Arabic news uses a special register: الفُصْحَى الإِعْلَامِيَّة (media standard Arabic) -- simpler than classical, more formal than colloquial. Listening to Al Jazeera for 20 minutes daily is the fastest path to native-level Arabic comprehension after formal study."},
