    grammar:[{
      title:"The Elative — أَفْعَل التَّفْضِيل (Comparative & Superlative)",
      type:"table",
      headers:["Base adj.","Elative (أَفْعَل)","Comparative use","Superlative use"],
      rows:[
        ["كَبِير (big)","أَكْبَر","هُوَ أَكْبَر مِنِّي","الأَكْبَر فِي العَائِلَة"],
        ["صَغِير (small)","أَصْغَر","أَصْغَر مِن أَخِيهِ","الأَصْغَر سِنًّا"],
        ["مَشْهُور (famous)","أَشْهَر","أَشْهَر مُحَقِّق","الأَشْهَر عَرَبِيًّا"],
        ["كَثِير (many)","أَكْثَر","أَكْثَر أَدِلَّة","الأَكْثَر أَهَمِّيَّة"],
        ["قَلِيل (few)","أَقَلّ","أَقَلّ مِن غَيْرِه","الأَقَلّ خِبْرَة"]
      ],
      note:"The elative (اسم التفضيل) uses the أَفْعَل pattern for both comparative and superlative. Comparative: أَفْعَل + مِن (than). Superlative: definite أَلْ + أَفْعَل OR أَفْعَل in iḍāfa: أَكْبَر المُدُن = the biggest of cities. The elative is invariable for gender/number (no ة, no plural) UNLESS it becomes an ordinary adjective, in which case feminine is فُعْلَى: أَكْبَر → كُبْرَى (greatest, fem.). ★ ELATIVE DRILL: Form أَفْعَل of: كَبِير، صَغِير، جَمِيل، سَرِيع، قَصِير، طَوِيل. ★ COMPARISON DRILL: Write: Cairo is bigger than Amman; the Quran is more eloquent than any human text; Ahmad is the funniest (أَطْرَف) in the group."
    }],
    speaking:{topic:"Narrate a crime story and solve it", promptAr:"اِرْوِ قِصَّة جَرِيمَة وَحُلَّهَا", promptEn:"Record 90 seconds: invent a short crime story. Describe the crime scene, the suspects, the evidence, and the resolution. Use passive voice at least 3 times and the elative at least twice (most suspicious, least evidence, etc.)."},
