      note:"Idioms often use derived forms that amplify meaning. زَيَّتَ (Form II of زَيْت = oil) = to oil/lubricate (metaphorically: to flatter). نَاقَشَ (Form III = discussed with) implies reciprocity — a two-way discussion. حَلَّقَ (Form II of حَلَقَة = circle/ring) = to soar/circle in the sky. Recognising the form helps decode unknown idioms. ★ FORM IDENTIFICATION DRILL: Identify the form number (I–X) of: كَتَبَ، قَدَّمَ، شَارَكَ، تَعَاوَنَ، انْكَسَرَ، اسْتَفَادَ، تَقَدَّمَ. ★ IDIOM DRILL: Use 3 idioms from this lesson in sentences. Identify the body part in each (رَأْس، قَلْب، عَيْن)."
